br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2h weapons should have double imbue points.</span><hr size=1> As subject title. 1h weapons you get less damage but benefit of using a shield or another weapon right. 2h weapons do more damage..so supposedly the tradeoff is even. But you can imbue that weapon and shield/weapon with a total of twice the amount of imbue points a 2h setup can have. Seeing as the majority of skalds use 2h weapons primarily this is a disadvantage for them and anyone else that uses a 2h weapon. It would be fair to make them double k thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmytheskald>Grimmytheskald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 9:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h weapons should have double imbue points.</span><hr size=1> It's actually an advantage to Midgard.<br>
<br>
Remember, the other two realms have to spend points to use one or two hand weapons.  Firbolgs with DonkeyKong hammers and Polearmsmen would agree with you.  I also think casters have it easy enough with cheap cloth armor.  They don't need any more imbue points out of a staff.<br>
<br>
I like being able to switch back and forth between the two.  Shield and one hander set up to take on casters, two hander is set up to take on mele. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.regal-image.com/customgraphics/grimnorbloodsong.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kergon>Kergon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h weapons should have double imbue points.</span><hr size=1> Isn't it funny that a shield is more useful vs a caster than it is vs a tank?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emblurr@teamskald>Emblurr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 12:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> And other realms 2 handers will do a considerable amount of more damage than ours. I'm primarily two hander as im sure most skalds are. When you change to 1h you can get say 60 odd imbue points worth. Thanes have this, warriors have this as they mostly shield users, then you have your zerkers and shadowblades who use two weapons majority and they all have the double imbue points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=albron>Albron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 12:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tyrantsonline.com/albron.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I agree with you Emblurr.   <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
HOOKED on speed!<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I don't agree. This has been an &quot;issue&quot; since the game started but I look at is a trade-off. You get a free damage bonus by using 2H weapons, why should there not be a disadvantage? <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kergon>Kergon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 1:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> There already is a disadvantage to using 2-handers, and it's huge... BT &amp; PBT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> No, that's a speed disadvantage. You get a bonus to damage specific to 2H weapons. There is no bonus to 1H weapons other than using a shield. Therefore I don't think that 2H weapons should recieve increase imbue points. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kergon>Kergon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 6:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Just like I said... they already have a disadvantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emblurr@teamskald>Emblurr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/4/03 8:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> I must have been under a rock coz I only heard someone mention yesterday. This isn't specifically targetted at skalds btw. And of course there are other advantages for using shields (not for us) like engage, slam, blocking etc. Still with bt, double imbue points I gotta refresh myself why I use 2h again ...oh yeah the big hits. I hope I can get one of those Dragon Shadow axes from Glacier. Would be so choice! Anyway this bit off track now was only over 2h weapons should be imbueable to the same amount as two 1h weapons or 1h + shield. I posted the same post on the vikings feedback on vn. Game on...splat some hibs and albs you guys! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></tabl